<topic id="embed-sqf-in-rng-xsd">
  <title>Embedding Schematron Quick Fixes in Relax NG or XML Schema</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Schematron Quick Fixes<indexterm>Embedded</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>SQF<indexterm>Embedded</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>Schematron <xref keyref="glossentry_quick-fix"><term>Quick Fixes</term></xref> can be
      embedded into an XML Schema through annotations (using the <codeph>appinfo</codeph> element),
      or in a Schematron rule embedded in the RELAX NG Schema. For more information about embedding
      Schematron in XML Schema or Relax NG, see <xref
        href="combined_RNG_and_SCH.dita#combined_RNG_and_SCH"/>.</p>
    <p><ph keyref="product"/> is able to extract and use the embedded Schematron <term>Quick
        Fixes</term>. To make the embedded Schematron <term>Quick Fixes</term> available, follow
      these steps:<ol>
        <li>Define a <xref
            href="validating-XML-documents-against-schema.dita#validating-XML-documents-against-schema"
            >validation against a schema</xref>.</li>
        <li>For the <uicontrol>Schema type</uicontrol>, choose <userinput>XML Schema</userinput> or
            <userinput>Relax NG</userinput>.</li>
        <li>Select the <uicontrol>Embedded Schematron rules</uicontrol> option.</li>
      </ol></p>
    <p><b>Example: Embedded Schematron Quick Fix in XML
      Schema</b><codeblock outputclass="language-xml">&lt;xsd:appinfo>
  &lt;sch:pattern>
    &lt;sch:rule context="...">
	&lt;sch:assert test="..." sqf:fix="fixId">Message.&lt;/sch:assert>
	  &lt;sqf:fix id="fixId">
	    ......
	  &lt;/sqf:fix>
    &lt;/sch:rule>
  &lt;/sch:pattern>
&lt;/xsd:appinfo></codeblock></p>
    <p><b>Example: Embedded Schematron Quick Fix in Relax
      NG</b><codeblock outputclass="language-xml">&lt;grammar 
    xmlns="http://relaxng.org/ns/structure/1.0"
    xmlns:sch="http://purl.oclc.org/dsdl/schematron" >
    &lt;sch:pattern>
      &lt;sch:rule context="...">
        &lt;sch:assert test="..." sqf:fix="fixId">Message.&lt;/sch:assert>
    	&lt;sqf:fix id="fixId">
    	  .....
    	&lt;/sqf:fix>
      &lt;/sch:rule>
     &lt;/sch:pattern>
     &lt;start>
      ..............
     &lt;/start>
&lt;/grammar></codeblock></p>
    <note type="tip">For more extensive examples, see the samples in the <filepath><term
          conkeyref="reusables-user-guide/oxy-install-dir"/>/samples/schematron</filepath>
      folder.</note>
  </body>
